Citation.sTitle: Heat capacity of vitreous and crystalline GeSe2 from 2 to 25K by relaxation calorimetry
Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacities of vitreous and crystalline GeSe2 as obtained by relaxation calorimetry from 2 to 25K are reported. Focus is given to the effect of the structure on the heat capacities and on the boson peaks observed for both vitreous and crystalline GeSe2 below 4 K. The accuracy of the commercial instrument used is considered by comparing the results obtained with earlier heat capacities determined by adiabatic calorimetry.
